<br>
In domains filled with neonates, it is not uncommon for a position such as primogen to switch hands quickly and often; it is a sign of how unstable these domains are. In domains with even the youngest claiming status, and Santa Carla is certainly one of these, it is unheard of for a Prince or Seneschal to &quot;skip out&quot;. As a member of the Camarilla, it is my duty and choice to sing the praises and to whisper of the hubris of my fellow Kindred. When both the Prince and the Seneschal disappear, enquiring minds want to know why.<br>
<br>
I have known two alastors as they earned their position, if Ms. Mercer-Renault and Mr. Blackmore have attained a position of such eminence, I will be glad to speak well of them and hold their names as shining examples of the Camarilla if I again meet them; if this is not the case, I'm sure the harpies will make more note than myself.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
Wallace Hoyt <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=storytellerscbn@scbnforum58570>storytellerscbn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Storyteller</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/03 3:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vital Message to all Kindred in Santa Carla</span><hr size=1> Herr Hoyt,<br>
<br>
Both Frau Mercer-Renald and Herr Blackmore have been asked rather insitently to take the mantle of Prinzessin and Seneschal in another Camarilla city.  Their location and the Camarilla Kollegium's resons for this are unknown to me at this time.  If an answer is forthcoming, I will, of course, inform the populace.  Until such time, we will all have to merely speculate.  The rumors and speculation, I fear, have already begun.  As Frauline Hart has pointed out, Alastors and Archons are not lightly made and I have not seen any evidence to support that as the case.  With all respect to Frau Mercer-Renald, can you see her hunting down and slaying Elder Kindred?  In this time of change, please, let us not place unnessecary and incorrect speculation where it is not useful.<br>
<br>
Graf Orlock<br>
