Kindred of Santa Carla,<br>
<br>
I assure those of you who have posted to this thread that I still retain the ability to read and have been watching its progress. While I can understand the suspicion and doubt that may fill some Kindred's minds concerning Ms. Mercer-Renald and I's departure from Santa Carla, I wish to assure the populace that there is little mystery behind its motivations. Santa Carla as a domain has grown in the last five months beneath Ms. Mercer-Renald's reign. I daresay the city has earned a good deal of respect in the eyes of the Camarilla as well. Unfortunately, these efforts have not gone unrecognized and like many Kindred are called to serve as Alastors and Archons, the Camarilla has called upon both Her Majesty and myself to serve another role.<br>
<br>
I assure you that Ms. Mercer-Renald and I thought long and hard upon the decision to accept this assignment. Were not such a capable Kindred as Count Orlock able to take over as Steward till a suitable ruler could be found in the city I daresay we would not have been able to accept these duties. There are places in the Camarilla that are much like Santa Carla's old unstable governments, and not all have had the benefit of months of stable rulership. These places require attention as well. The Elders know this and they do what they feel is best for the Camarilla. Ms. Mercer-Renald and I are both in Clans that do not often enjoy the luxury of having personal freedoms to move where we wish to move. <b>We do what we are told by our Elders.</b> This is a lesson that many Kindred in Santa Carla can still benefit from.<br>
<br>
It is my belief that there are those among the Camarilla who wish to test Santa Carla's resolve. To test if the city is capable of retaining its Camarilla Tradition, its Primogen Council, and its stable order, despite having the two officers who uphold those most directly, removed. There are many of you who see "being Camarilla" as a function of which leaders are in power. You could not be more wrong. "Being Camarilla" means retaining those same values and order, despite who rules your city. The Traditions and the desire to retain Camarilla power must pervade among the whole of the populace. If all Kindred in Santa Carla are true to that purpose, then a new Prince will be chosen and the city will continue what has been started. Then, I believe, it will be truly ready to be acknowledged as a rightful member of this society.<br>
<br>
Lastly. I have heard assertations that Her Majesty and I are "skipping out". I find such assertations to be completely and utterly insulting. Count Orlock. I ask you to find out the names of those individuals who would say that I have shirked my responsibilities to the Camarilla in any way. I assure you when I return to Santa Carla, and its very likely I someday will, I make each Kindred who I find out about saying such things a promise that I will show them exactly how little they do understand about my will and my sense of duty to the Camarilla. So, if you wish to take your jabs and your shots in our absence, then do so. But I promise you that whatever short-term gains you will reap will not be worth what you are sowing.<br>
<br>
I will be posting more details concerning Ms. Mercer-Renald and I's duties when I am able.<br>
<br>
Eternally,<br>
<br>
Grifon Blackmore<br>
Clan Ventrue <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=18.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.showNextMessage?topicID=18.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/de/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.threadControl?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/de/themes/default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="scbnforum58570frm12">Blackjack's Message Board <option value="scbnforum58570frm21">The Barrens<option value="scbnforum58570frm23">Domain Status<option value="scbnforum58570frm20">SchreckNET™ (Nos only)<option value="scbnforum58570frm18">The Santa Carla Tribune<option value="scbnforum58570frm19">Literary<option value="scbnforum58570frm16">Players Forum<option value="scbnforum58570frm17">Storyteller and Narrator Announcements</select></td><td><input type=s